title: Pedrosa wins Malaysia MotoGP, world title still up for grabs
text:
Pedrosa wins Malaysia MotoGP, world title still up for grabs Published: 25 October 2015 3:53 PM 
Spain's Dani Pedrosa lead throughout the entire race at Sepang. – Reuters pic, October 25, 2015. Spain's Dani Pedrosa won the Malaysian MotoGP today, starting in pole position and leading throughout the entire race. 
But the world title remained up for grabs, with Jorge Lorenzo taking second, cutting championship leader Valentino Rossi's points advantage down to just seven. – AFP, October 25, 2015.
